# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ANDROID — Option A: adb (recommended for USB-connected Android, e.g. Poco/Xiaomi)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Mac setup:
#   1. brew install android-platform-tools
#   2. Verify: which adb  →  /opt/homebrew/bin/adb
#   3. Set OTP_MODE=adb in this file
#
# Phone setup (Poco / Xiaomi / HyperOS):
#   1. Settings → About phone → tap MIUI/HyperOS version 7 times
#   2. Settings → Additional settings → Developer options
#   3. Enable: USB debugging
#   4. Enable: USB debugging (Security settings)   ← required on Xiaomi/POCO
#   5. Connect phone to PC with a data USB cable
#   6. On phone popup: tap "Allow USB debugging" → check "Always allow"
#   7. On PC verify: adb devices
#      Expected: XXXXXXXX    device
#   (Windows: if "unauthorized", install phone USB driver from manufacturer or use File Transfer mode)
#
# Run booking:
#   npm run book:api
